Dr Westenfelt:  But why did you do it █████?
附加记录：    



Dr P█████:  Quite frankly I didn't expect the rollercoaster I got.
附加记录：    



Dr Westenfelt:  Rollercoaster?
附加记录：    



Dr P█████:  Well yeah, A███ said that they were safe to wear. Guess he didn't have to wear them much when they were looking for (A Brief Pause) magic?
附加记录：    



Dr Westenfelt:  Thaumatic signatures, yeah.
附加记录：    



Dr P█████:  (Chuckles) Well that's Yorkshire for you.
附加记录：    



(Both doctors continue the friendly conversation for a while until Dr Westenfelt redirects back to the main topic)
附加记录：    



Dr Westenfelt:  So how was the experience?
附加记录：    



Dr P█████:  Nice at first. Everybody wants to stress a little less, but it just got worse.
附加记录：    



Dr Westenfelt:  Could you define  for me?
附加记录：    



Dr P█████:  Well, okay. So imagine being a tad bit drunk, but all the time. You are happy, warm, not a care in the world. Yet you know that people are looking at you a little funny, but that doesn't make you want to stop, right? You consider it, so you take 'em off but the world is just so painstakingly dull. Before you know it they're right back on your face and you won't think about this again for a week. It was like that if that makes any sense.
附加记录：    



Dr Westenfelt:  Would you consider using (SCP-5127) again?
附加记录：    



Dr P█████:  Well maybe. (A Brief Pause) Actually no. Not unless I needed to. In fact, keep it away from me, okay? I know that withdrawal gets worse before it gets better and I don't want easy access to it in case I start slipping.
