Dr P█████ was afterwards demoted to E-class for initial quarantine and assessment. Dr P█████ has since been rehabilitated and has resumed his research at Site-64 after returning to C-class status. At his request, Containment Committee Order 5127.S64.15.1 remains in place.

Addendum 5127.2: After approximately 14 hours of accidental direct light exposure, the concentration of SCP-5127-1 in Site-64's anomalous object lockerroom was dense enough to incapacitate Dr Berg and two of his research personnel. This initiated a level 3 evacuation of Site-64's northern quadrant until sufficient ventilation could be provided. SCP-5127-1 was subsequently reclassified as a vapour, and containment protocol was updated accordingly. Dr Berg's consequent request to process SCP-5127 as a possible biochemical weapon has been denied.

Addendum 5127.3:  While being tested at Site-91, Dr A███ remarked on how SCP-5127's euphoria-inducing qualities could be implicated to assist any individuals infected with SCP-4042-2 continue.

Scribe's note: This document was originally composed at Site-91 before being amended and completed by Site-64. SCP-5127 was originally contained and documented in the United Kingdom before being transferred to a facility in the United States. Therefore, it is composed in British-English to preserve its comprehensive integrity.

